```mermaid
graph LR
  UI[Streamlit UI (ui/app.py)] -->|calls| Engine[Simulation Engine (ui/simulation_engine.py)]
  Engine -->|uses| Data[Local Data / Records (record.py, res/)]
  Engine -->|calls LLM| Groq[Groq API (GROQ_API_KEY)]
  Engine -->|logs| Logs[log/*]
  subgraph Backend
    Engine
    Data
    Logs
  end
  subgraph LLM Providers
    Groq
    Gemini[Google Gemini]
    Mock[MockLLM]
  end
  UI -->|chat| Chat[StockAIAdvisor (ui/chatbot.py)]
  Chat -->|selects| Groq
  Chat -->|fallback| Mock
```

---

Notes:
- The UI (`ui/app.py`) is the Streamlit entrypoint and calls into the `SimulationEngine` for configuration and run control.
- `SimulationEngine` may call an LLM provider when `GROQ_API_KEY` is configured; otherwise it falls back to `MockLLM`.
- Persistent records and logs are saved under `res/` and `log/`.
